  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Shared Aid Fund for Emergency Response (SAFER)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SAFER supports local organisations to raise funds for humanitarian response in the Philippines.  In the past two years, Philippines has not called for international assistance for humanitarian responses which makes it difficult for local organisations to respond to affected communities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Shared Aid Fund for Emergency Response (SAFER) is a collaborative initiative among the largest NGO networks in the Philippines, namely: CODE-NGO, Humanitarian Response Consortium (HRC) and NASSA-Caritas Philippines. Soon to be registered as a Foundation, SAFER aims to establish itself as a locally-driven fundraising mechanism managed by Filipinos for Filipinos. 
SAFER aims to raise funds to address the needs of communities affected by disasters and the deliver the most appropriate humanitarian assistance to where it is needed, and thus help uplift the dignity of survivors of disasters and emergencies.</narrative>
  </description>
